---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import Icon from '../../components/Icon.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Quick Start // System Init"
  description="Install ostk and boot the OS on any git repository in under 5 minutes."
  sectionLabel="INITIALIZATION_SEQUENCE // 01"
>
  <p class="font-body text-sm text-secondary max-w-xl mb-12">
    Zero to running agents in 5 minutes. The ostk kernel coordinates distributed AI agents through a cryptographic archive protocol.
  </p>

  <!-- Prerequisites Manifest -->
  <div class="bg-surface-container-low p-6 mb-12 border-l-2 border-primary max-w-sm">
    <h3 class="section-label-secondary mb-4">PREREQUISITES_MANIFEST</h3>
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <div class="flex justify-between font-body text-xs">
        <span class="text-secondary">ENVIRONMENT</span>
        <span class="text-on-surface">macOS / Linux</span>
      </div>
      <div class="flex justify-between font-body text-xs">
        <span class="text-secondary">NETWORK_TRANS</span>
        <span class="text-on-surface">curl</span>
      </div>
      <div class="flex justify-between font-body text-xs">
        <span class="text-secondary">VERSION_CTRL</span>
        <span class="text-on-surface">git 2.39+</span>
      </div>
      <div class="flex justify-between font-body text-xs">
        <span class="text-secondary">AUTH_TIER</span>
        <span class="text-on-surface">GPG signing (optional)</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="font-body text-[10px] text-outline mt-2">
      GPG is optional. Without it you boot at <a href="/docs/trust-model" class="text-primary hover:underline">T2 (read-only)</a>. With a GPG key you get T1 write access. With a cross-signed key you get T0 full governance.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Step 01: Install -->
  <section class="mb-16">
    <div class="flex items-baseline gap-4 mb-6">
      <span class="serif-text text-4xl font-bold text-primary">01</span>
      <h2 class="serif-text text-2xl font-medium text-on-surface">INSTALL_BINARIES</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-surface-container-lowest p-4 border border-surface-variant mb-4">
      <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-2">
        <span class="font-label text-[10px] text-secondary">SHELL</span>
      </div>
      <code class="font-body text-sm text-primary">curl -fsSL https://ostk.ai/install.sh | sh</code>
    </div>
    <p class="font-body text-xs text-secondary max-w-lg">
      The script detects your platform, downloads the correct binary, verifies its GPG signature, and places it in your <code class="text-primary">$PATH</code>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Step 02: Initialize -->
  <section class="mb-16">
    <div class="flex items-baseline gap-4 mb-6">
      <span class="serif-text text-4xl font-bold text-primary">02</span>
      <h2 class="serif-text text-2xl font-medium text-on-surface">INITIALIZE_WORKSPACE</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-4">
      <div class="bg-surface-container p-6">
        <h3 class="font-body text-sm text-primary font-bold mb-2">AUTOMATIC_DETECTION</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-xs text-secondary mb-4">
          Best for local development and single-node archives.
        </p>
        <code class="font-body text-sm text-on-surface">ostk init</code>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-surface-container p-6">
        <h3 class="font-body text-sm text-primary font-bold mb-2">GUIDED_CONFIG</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-xs text-secondary mb-4">
          7-step manual setup for distributed multi-agent clusters.
        </p>
        <code class="font-body text-sm text-on-surface">ostk init --guided</code>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="font-body text-xs text-secondary max-w-lg">
      Both modes create <code class="text-primary">.ostk/</code> with your
      <a href="/docs/humanfile" class="text-primary hover:underline">HUMANFILE</a>,
      <a href="/docs/agentfile" class="text-primary hover:underline">Agentfile</a>,
      <code class="text-primary">pin.caps</code>, and
      <a href="/docs/ostk-toml" class="text-primary hover:underline">ostk.toml</a>.
      Use <code class="text-primary">--guided</code> on your first project.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Step 03: Boot -->
  <section class="mb-16">
    <div class="flex items-baseline gap-4 mb-6">
      <span class="serif-text text-4xl font-bold text-primary">03</span>
      <h2 class="serif-text text-2xl font-medium text-on-surface">SYSTEM_BOOT</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-surface-container-lowest p-4 border border-surface-variant mb-4">
      <div class="font-label text-[10px] text-secondary mb-2">SHELL</div>
      <code class="font-body text-sm text-primary">ostk boot</code>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-surface-container-low p-4 mb-4">
      <div class="font-label text-[10px] text-secondary mb-3">EXPECTED_OUTPUT</div>
      <div class="font-body text-[11px] leading-relaxed text-secondary space-y-1">
        <p>boot: reaped 3 dead agent(s) from process table</p>
        <p><span class="text-primary">✓</span> HUMANFILE loaded (global only)</p>
        <p>HUMANFILE: ✓ verified (T0), project unsigned</p>
        <p>trust: T1 (cross-signed, write access)</p>
        <p>driver rust: inactive (demand-spawn on first use)</p>
        <p>.language: 58 verbs | fleet: 0 alive</p>
        <p>needles: 0 open</p>
        <p>boot confidence: 0.00 (restricted mode)</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="font-body text-xs text-secondary max-w-lg">
      Loads state from <code class="text-primary">.ostk/</code>, detects your trust tier, and prints a status report. No configuration file needed. The OS reads the repo and orients.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Step 04: Launch Interface -->
  <section class="mb-16">
    <div class="flex items-baseline gap-4 mb-6">
      <span class="serif-text text-4xl font-bold text-primary">04</span>
      <h2 class="serif-text text-2xl font-medium text-on-surface">LAUNCH_INTERFACE</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-surface-container-lowest p-4 border border-surface-variant mb-4">
      <div class="font-label text-[10px] text-secondary mb-2">SHELL</div>
      <code class="font-body text-sm text-primary">ostk tui</code>
    </div>
    <p class="font-body text-xs text-secondary max-w-lg mb-4">
      The <a href="/docs/tui" class="text-primary hover:underline">ostk tui</a> is your central command deck. Monitor the fleet, dispatch work via the <a href="/features/tack" class="text-primary hover:underline">tack bar</a>, and approve <a href="/docs/trust-model" class="text-primary hover:underline">permission gates</a> in real-time.
    </p>
    <p class="font-body text-xs text-secondary max-w-lg">
      From here, spawn your first agent: <code class="text-primary">ostk kernel spawn worker --model sonnet --budget 2 "Fix the bug described in →001"</code>. See <a href="/docs/commands" class="text-primary hover:underline">Commands</a> for the full reference.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Troubleshooting -->
  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="section-label mb-4">TROUBLESHOOTING</h2>
    <div class="bg-surface-container-low p-6 border-l-2 border-primary">
      {[
        { issue: 'Boot shows T3 (anonymous)', fix: 'You have no GPG key. Generate one: gpg --full-generate-key. Then re-run ostk boot.' },
        { issue: 'Boot shows T2 (read-only)', fix: 'Your GPG key exists but is not cross-signed by a T0 holder. Ask the project owner to sign your key.' },
        { issue: '"bail download failed"', fix: 'Network issue fetching governance package. ostk uses defaults. Re-run ostk init when connected.' },
        { issue: '"version mismatch"', fix: 'Your binary is older than ostk.toml requires. Update: cargo install ostk or re-run the install script.' },
      ].map(t => (
        <div class="flex gap-6 text-xs font-body py-3 border-b border-surface-variant">
          <span class="text-error w-56 shrink-0">{t.issue}</span>
          <span class="text-secondary">{t.fix}</span>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Next Sequences -->
  <div class="metadata-ribbon border-t border-surface-variant">
    <span class="font-label text-[10px] text-secondary mr-4">NEXT_SEQUENCES:</span>
    <a href="/docs/trust-model">
      <Icon name="shield" size="14" class="align-middle mr-1" />
      TRUST_MODEL
    </a>
    <a href="/docs/commands">
      <Icon name="terminal" size="14" class="align-middle mr-1" />
      COMMANDS
    </a>
    <a href="/docs/humanfile">
      <Icon name="person" size="14" class="align-middle mr-1" />
      HUMANFILE
    </a>
    <a href="/docs/tui">
      <Icon name="tv" size="14" class="align-middle mr-1" />
      TUI_GUIDE
    </a>
  </div>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "HowTo",
    "name": "Install and Boot ostk",
    "description": "Install ostk and boot the OS on any git repository in under 5 minutes.",
    "totalTime": "PT5M",
    "step": [
      { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Install", "text": "Run: curl -fsSL https://ostk.ai/install.sh | sh" },
      { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Initialize", "text": "Run: ostk init (or ostk init --guided for interactive setup)" },
      { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Boot", "text": "Run: ostk boot — loads state, detects trust tier, prints status" },
      { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Launch Interface", "text": "Run: ostk tui — opens the terminal command deck" }
    ]
  })} />
</DocsLayout>
